  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best way make extra money?",
  "response": "Making extra money can be approached in various ways depending on your skills, interests, and available time. Here are some popular methods:\n\n1. **Freelancing**: Utilize your skills (writing, graphic design, programming, marketing, etc.) on platforms like Upwork, Fiverr, or Freelancer.\n\n2. **Online Tutoring**: Teach subjects you're knowledgeable in or offer lessons in areas like music, languages, or test preparation through platforms like VIPKid, Tutor.com, or Wyzant.\n\n3. **Gig Economy Jobs**: Work for companies like Uber, Lyft, DoorDash, or Postmates that allow you to earn money on a flexible schedule.\n\n4. **Selling Products**: Sell items online through sites like eBay, Etsy, or Facebook Marketplace. You can sell handcrafted goods, vintage items, or even things you no longer need.\n\n5. **Affiliate Marketing**: Promote products or services and earn a commission for every sale made through your referral link. You can do this through a blog, social media, or YouTube.\n\n6. **Real Estate Investments**: If you have some capital, consider investing in real estate or exploring options like rental properties or REITs (Real Estate Investment Trusts).\n\n7. **Pet Sitting or Dog Walking**: Use platforms like Rover or Wag to connect with pet owners needing services.\n\n8. **Remote Work**: Look for part-time remote job opportunities or side gigs that can be done from home.\n\n9. **Surveys and Market Research**: Participate in online surveys or research studies through sites like Swagbucks, Survey Junkie, or Amazon Mechanical Turk.\n\n10. **Renting Your Space**: If you have extra room, consider listing it on Airbnb or another vacation rental site.\n\n11. **Dropshipping**: Start an online store without holding inventory by partnering with suppliers who ship products directly to customers.\n\n12. **Investing**: If you understand financial markets, consider investing in stocks, bonds, or mutual funds to grow your money over time (be aware of risks).\n\nBefore starting any of these ventures, make sure to evaluate the time commitment, potential earnings, and any applicable legal or tax implications.",
